The Nigerian National Summit Group (NNSG) has said that the reason giving by the presiding bishop of the Living Faith Church, Bishop David Oyedepo, for holding normal church services last Sunday was untenable. NNSG said that the cleric disregard of the ban on large gatherings gave the church in Nigeria a very bad image and the government should arrest him to let the world know that we are taking the coronavirus threat seriously. He said that his arrest would show to all Nigerians that nobody is above the law. In a statement the group sent to LEADERSHIP through its scribe, Mr. Tony Uranta, it stated that Oyedepo’s decision has “irredeemably belittled him in one’s eyes, and the federal government will be shirking its primary responsibly of keeping Nigerians secure if the bishop is allowed to get away with this one act which must have put, at least, thousands of gullible Nigerians that heeded his call to worship-as-usual in danger, not to even begin to imagine, at least, tens of thousands of other Nigerians that these ones could make secondary contacts for this scary disease! “Bishop Oyedepo is one of my respected Nigerian Christian leaders, but his excuse for disobeying the commonsensical Federal Government of Nigerian ban on large gatherings gave the church in Nigeria a very bad image and the government should arrest him to let the world know that we are taking the coronavirus threat seriously, and prove to all Nigerians that nobody is above the law, especially in this dire season of the global pandemic,” he said.